The Real Dirt on Farmer John;;78;;88;;NC;;Filmmaker Taggart Siegel captures two turbulent decades in the life of John Peterson, an Illinois farmer who not only tends the land but also delves into writing and performance art. A man who would as soon work the fields in a feather boa as in a pair of jeans, Peterson rises out of the bankruptcy and depression plaguing Midwest farm communities in the 1980s and saves his livelihood through organic agriculture.;;Documentary;;Taggart Siegel;;2005;;NC;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_real_dirt_on_farmer_john_2007